Key Match Events: The Spurs lost to the Mavericks 110-93, with Victor Wembanyama not in the lineup due to a right knee contusion.
Pre-Game Insights: Spurs interim coach Mitch Johnson said 'a lot of minutes and a lot of shots' will change without Wembanyama, and that 'guys need to step up' and 'we need to move the ball, probably play fast and try to continue to maintain our spacing.'
Post-Match Reflections: Interim coach Mitch Johnson did not provide any post-match reflections in the article.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Victor Wembanyama leads the Spurs averaging 22.7 points and 10.5 rebounds per game, and he leads the NBA averaging 3.7 blocks per game.
Others: Zach Collins was scheduled to start in Wembanyama's place, and the Spurs' next game will be Tuesday at home against Oklahoma City.
